{"word":"ἀπόθεσις","slug":"ἀπόθεσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπόθεσις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀποτίθημι'><el>ἀποτίθημι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a laying up in store</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a putting aside, getting rid of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>= <a href='S:ἀποδυτήριον'><el>ἀποδυτήριον</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}